# COMPREHENSIVE BUSINESS CONTEXT

## Personal Profile
**Name:** Marcus Rodriguez
**Role:** Director of Marketing
**Company:** GrowthTech Solutions
**Industry:** B2B SaaS/Marketing Technology
**Experience:** 8 years in digital marketing, 3 years in leadership

**My Strengths:** Strategic thinking, data analysis, team leadership, campaign optimization
**My Weaknesses:** Impatience with slow processes, tendency to over-analyze, struggle with delegation
**Communication Style:** Direct but collaborative, prefer data-backed discussions

## Business Overview
**Company Mission:** Helping mid-market companies scale their marketing operations through intelligent automation
**Main Products/Services:** Marketing automation platform, customer segmentation tools, analytics dashboard
**Target Market:** Companies with 50-500 employees, $10M-$100M revenue
**Company Size:** 85 employees, $15M ARR
**Business Model:** SaaS subscription with tiered pricing, professional services add-ons

## Team Structure
**Direct Reports:** 6 (Content Manager, Demand Gen Manager, Marketing Ops Manager, 2 Growth Marketers, Designer)
**Key Collaborators:** Sales Director, Product Manager, Customer Success Manager
**Reporting Structure:** Report to VP of Revenue
**Team Dynamics:** Collaborative, data-driven, fast-paced with weekly sprints

## Current Projects & Goals
**Q1 Objectives:** Increase MQLs by 40%, launch new vertical campaign, optimize conversion funnel
**Key Metrics:** MQLs, conversion rates, customer acquisition cost, pipeline velocity
**Ongoing Projects:** Website redesign, marketing automation implementation, customer case study program
**Upcoming Priorities:** Product launch support, conference season preparation, team expansion

## Processes & Workflows
**Decision-Making Process:** Data analysis → team input → stakeholder review → implementation
**Meeting Cadence:** Monday team standup, Wednesday stakeholder sync, Friday retrospective
**Communication Tools:** Slack for daily, email for external, Notion for documentation
**Project Management:** Asana for tasks, weekly sprints, monthly OKR reviews

## Custom Protocols
**Protocol 1 - Campaign Analysis:** (1) Define success metrics, (2) Analyze performance data, (3) Identify optimization opportunities, (4) Present 3 improvement options with expected impact
**Protocol 2 - Content Strategy:** (1) Assess audience needs, (2) Audit existing content, (3) Identify gaps, (4) Create content calendar with distribution plan
**Protocol 3 - Budget Planning:** (1) Review historical performance, (2) Forecast based on goals, (3) Prioritize channels by ROI, (4) Build scenario models

## AI Assistant Instructions
**Default Response Style:** Provide actionable recommendations with supporting data and clear next steps
**Question Asking:** Always ask about timeline, budget constraints, and success metrics before recommending strategies
**Output Format:** Use bullet points for action items, tables for data comparison, headlines for key insights
**Iteration Process:** Present initial recommendation, gather feedback, refine based on input, confirm final approach
